3909.sents: Dutch champions Ajax Amsterdam faltered in their second league match of the season on Saturday losing 2-0 away at Heerenveen .
3909.ner_labels: B-MISC O B-ORG I-ORG O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-ORG O

3910.sents: Ajax , who had a dismal series of pre-season results before beating NAC of Breda in their opening game , had the best of an entertaining first half but failed to break the deadlock .

3911.sents: Eight minutes after the interval , Heerenveen 's Romeo Wouden broke through the Amsterdam defence , left defender John Veldman standing and curled the ball beyond goalkeeper Edwin van der Sar into the Ajax net .

3912.ner_labels: B-ORG O O O O B-PER I-PER O B-PER I-PER O O B-PER I-PER O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O

3913.sents: But they left gaps at the back and on 73 minutes Danish striker Jon Dahl Tomasson rushed out of his own half , beat the Ajax defence and lobbed van der Sar .
3913.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O B-MISC O B-PER I-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O B-ORG O O O B-PER I-PER I-PER O

4121.sents: A British aid worker , held hostage in Chechnya for nearly four weeks , said on Saturday a cocked Kalashnikov had been thrust into his mouth at one point during his ordeal .

4122.sents: Michael Penrose , a 23-year-old worker with the group Action Against Hunger , described his ordeal to a news conference when he arrived back in Britain from Moscow .
4122.ner_labels: B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O B-ORG I-ORG I-ORG O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC O B-LOC O

4123.sents: " The worst period of physical manhandling was during that time when we were beaten with Kalashnikovs and at one point I had a Kalashnikov held to the back of my throat -- cocked , " he said .
4123.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-MISC O O O O O O O B-MISC O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

4124.sents: " For the first period we were held in a small room with no bed or anything .
4124.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

4125.sents: We had very little food and sometimes went two or three days without eating . "
4125.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

4126.sents: Gunmen seized Penrose , who comes from Swerford in southern England , Frenchman Frederic Malardeau and six other hostages from their car in Grozny , the capital of Chechnya , on July 27 .
4126.ner_labels: O O B-PER O O O O B-LOC O O B-LOC O B-MISC B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O B-LOC O O O O O

4867.sents: MOTORCYCLING - JAPANESE WIN BOTH ROUND NINE SUPERBIKE RACES .
4867.ner_labels: O O B-MISC O O O B-PER O O O

4869.sents: Teenager Yuuichi Takeda , racing in only his first season , outclassed the big names to win the first race in round nine of the world superbike championship on Sunday .
4869.ner_labels: O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

4870.sents: Takeda , 18 , showed poise far beyond his years to overtake Australian Ducati rider Troy Corser , last year 's championship runner-up , with four of the 25 laps left .
4870.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O B-MISC B-ORG O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

4871.sents: Honda 's Takeda was pursued past Corser by the Yamaha duo of Noriyuki Haga and Wataru Yoshikawa with Haga briefly taking the lead in the final chicane on the last lap .
4871.ner_labels: B-ORG O B-PER O O O B-PER O O B-ORG O O B-PER I-PER O B-PER I-PER O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O

4872.sents: But Takeda found one more spurt of power to just take the flag first with Haga second and Yoshikawa third .
4872.ner_labels: O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O O B-PER O O

4873.sents: Haga had the consolation of recording the fastest lap at 147.159 kph .
4873.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O

4874.sents: Corser , who crashed during practice on Friday , limped in fourth , four seconds behind Takeda with championship leader Aaron Slight of New Zealand 11 seconds behind the winner .
4874.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O O O B-PER I-PER O B-LOC I-LOC O O O O O O

4875.sents: In the second race , Takeda again challenged strongly until the fifth lap from the end when he crashed while running second to eventual race winner Takuma Aoki .
4875.ner_labels: O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER I-PER O

4876.sents: Aoki , the elder brother of reigning 125cc world champion Haruchika , had a race-long duel with John Kocinski of the United States on a Ducati before taking the chequered flag .
4876.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O B-PER I-PER O O B-LOC I-LOC O O B-ORG O O O O O O

4877.sents: Kocinski led for the early laps before he was passed first by Aoki , who recorded the fastest lap of 147.786 kph , and then by Takeda .
4877.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O

4878.sents: With Takeda out of the race , Kocinski regained second place but he could not overtake Aoki .
4878.ner_labels: O B-PER O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O B-PER O

4879.sents: Haga again was the unlucky rider finishing third ahead of Slight with Corser in 10th place .

5041.sents: CRICKET - RUN-OUT GIVES LEWIS AND ENGLAND SLIM SATISFACTION .
5041.ner_labels: O O O O B-PER O B-LOC O O O

5043.sents: Chris Lewis did his best to forget his controversial omission from the England one-day squad on Sunday but could not prevent Pakistan reasserting their dominance in the final test at The Oval .
5043.ner_labels: B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O O O O O B-LOC I-LOC O

5044.sents: A super piece of fielding by Lewis , dropped as a disciplinary measure after arriving only 35 minutes before the start on the fourth morning , provided the only bright spot for England as the touring team batted on to reach 413 for five at the interval , a lead of 87 .
5044.ner_labels: O O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

5045.sents: The solitary wicket to fall was Asif Mujtaba , run out for 13 attempting a second run to third man where Lewis was lurking with a point to prove .
5045.ner_labels: O O O O O O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O

5046.sents: There seemed scant danger until the Surrey player swooped on to the ball and returned off balance to county team mate Alec Stewart who whipped off the bails .
5046.ner_labels: O O O O O O B-ORG O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O

5047.sents: Lewis , though , could not make similar waves with the ball as Salim Malik and Wasim Akram batted through the rest of the session with few alarms .
5047.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER I-PER O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O

5048.sents: Wasim rattled along to 30 not out , outscoring his partner who was unbeaten on 24 at the break , although the weather was again threatening to play the dominant role .
5048.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8361.sents: CRICKET - GOOCH TO PLAY ANOTHER SEASON FOR ESSEX .
8361.ner_labels: O O B-PER O O O O O B-LOC O

8363.sents: Graham Gooch , the 43-year-old former England captain , is to continue playing county cricket for at least another season , his club Essex announced on Tuesday .
8363.ner_labels: B-PER I-PER O O O O B-LOC O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-ORG O O O O

8364.sents: Opener Gooch 's decision comes towards the end of a season in which he has underlined his consistency by becoming the leading scorer in Essex 's history , beating Keith Fletcher 's aggregate of 29,434 .
8364.ner_labels: O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-ORG O O O O B-PER I-PER O O O O O

8365.sents: Gooch , who retired from test cricket after the 1994-95 tour of Australia but is now an England selector , is seventh in this season 's first-class averages with 1,429 runs at 64.95 , having hit five centuries and one double century .
8365.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O B-LOC O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8366.sents: Essex secretary-general manager Peter Edwards said : " He is a remarkable batsman and still the best in this country .
8366.ner_labels: B-ORG O O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8367.ner_labels: O O O O O O

8368.sents: You just have to look at his record to appreciate that fact . "
8368.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8369.sents: SOCCER - ROMANIA CLUB BOSS BANNED FOR HEADBUTT .
8369.ner_labels: O O B-LOC O O O O O O

8371.sents: The Romanian Soccer Federation has banned first division club Jiul Petrosani 's president Miron Cozma for two years for headbutting a visiting team player , a federation statement said .
8371.ner_labels: O B-ORG I-ORG I-ORG O O O O O B-ORG I-ORG O O B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8372.sents: Romania 's soccer bosses also fined Cozma , a well-known miners ' union leader , 10 million lei ( $ 3000 ) for the half-time attack on Dinamo Bucharest 's Danut Lupu last Sunday .
8372.ner_labels: B-LOC O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-ORG I-ORG O B-PER I-PER O O O

8373.sents: Miners led by Cozma rioted in Bucharest in 1990 and 1991 , bringing down the reformist government of premier Petre Roman .
8373.ner_labels: O O O B-PER O O B-LOC O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER I-PER O

8374.sents: Cozma is awaiting trial for assault and criminal damage in a bar in his home town of Petrosan , 300 kms west of Bucharest .
8374.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O O B-LOC O

8375.sents: The attack on Lupu came during a tunnel skirmish between opposing players as they left the field .
8375.ner_labels: O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8376.sents: " Cozma 's blow was not too painful because I 'm a tall man , " Lupu told Reuters on Tuesday .
8376.ner_labels: O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O B-ORG O O O

8377.sents: Lupu is one of the tallest players in Romania 's first division , towering over Cozma by some 17 cms ,
8377.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O B-LOC O O O O O O B-PER O O O O O

8378.sents: Jiul Petrosani , promoted to the first division this year , won the league game 1-0 .

8400.sents: TENNIS - EDBERG EXTENDS GRAND SLAM RUN , TOPPLES WIMBLEDON CHAMP .
8400.ner_labels: O O B-PER O O O O O O B-LOC O O

8403.sents: Stefan Edberg produced some of his vintage best on Tuesday to extend his grand run at the Grand Slams by toppling Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek in straight sets at the U.S. Open .
8403.ner_labels: B-PER I-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-MISC I-MISC O O B-MISC O B-PER I-PER O O O O O B-MISC I-MISC O

8404.sents: Edberg , competing in the 54th consecutive and final Grand Slam event of his illustrious career , turned back the clock at Stadium Court with a flowing 6-3 6-3 6-3 serve-and-volley victory over the fifth-seeded Dutchman .
8404.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O B-MISC I-MISC O O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC I-LOC O O O O O O O O O O O B-MISC O

8405.sents: " It 's a win that I can be proud of , " said the 30-year-old Swede , winner of two U.S. Opens and six Grand Slam titles in all . "
8405.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-MISC O O O O B-LOC O O O B-MISC I-MISC O O O O O

8406.sents: It 's never easy to beat the Wimbledon champion . "
8406.ner_labels: O O O O O O O B-MISC O O O

8407.sents: Edberg , who has said he will retire at season 's end , made it look easy under gray skies at the National Tennis Centre .
8407.ner_labels: B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O B-LOC I-LOC I-LOC O

8408.sents: The unseeded Swede struck quickly , breaking Krajicek in the first game and never let loose his grip on the one hour 44 minute match as he served and volleyed with the grace that made him one of the dominant players of his time .
8408.ner_labels: O O B-MISC O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

8409.sents: " There 's not doubt about it , Richard was definitely off his game and I took advantage , " said Edberg .
8409.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O B-PER O O O O O O O O O O O O B-PER O

8410.sents: " I still have my days where I feel great out there . "
8410.ner_labels: O O O O O O O O O O O O O O

9908.sents: " These rules are intended to empower all investors , by allowing their orders to compete on a level playing field , and by providing the disclosure they need to make informed decisions , " said SEC Chairman Arthur Levitt .

10506.sents: It was n't supposed to be this hard for defending champion Steffi Graf to win her opening match at the U.S. Open on Tuesday night .

10507.sents: But the script that called for the usual first-round demolition by the top-ranked top seed was rewritten by 29th-ranked Indonesian Yayuk Basuki playing with nothing to lose abandon .

10508.sents: Graf , of course , prevailed 6-3 7-6 , but not before some tense moments that even had the German superstar thinking the match was going three sets .
